    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nI'd like to put my `vim.lsp.enable()` calls in my `after/ftplugin/*.lua` files, but it doesn't seem to work that way? Not sure if this is intended, maybe the docs could point out where the code snippets it shows should live, if it's intended to only be in users init file?\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nIn `~/.config/nvim/init.lua`:\n\n```lua\nvim.lsp.config['luals'] = {\n  cmd = { 'lua-language-server' },\n  filetypes = { 'lua' },\n  root_markers = { '.luarc.json', '.luarc.jsonc', '.stylua.toml', 'stylua.toml', '.luacheckrc', '.git' },\n  settings = {\n    Lua = {\n      runtime = {\n        version = 'LuaJIT',\n      },\n    },\n  },\n}\n```\n\nIn `~/.config/nvim/after/ftplugin/lua.lua`:\n\n```lua\nvim.lsp.enable('luals')\n```\n\nCheck that the server wasn't started with:\n\n```\n:=vim.lsp.get_clients()[1].server_capabilities\n```\n\nBut if we move the `vim.lsp.enable('luals')` into the `init.lua` file, it works.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nAdding `vim.lsp.enable()` call in `after/ftplugin/*.lua` should be possible\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.11.0 commit g38f554e9c4\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nn/a\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nsource",
